Its funny how your best friends can make you feel so bad about yourself, just by being perfect. Don't get me wrong i love my friends so much but being surrounded by beauty all the time just makes you feel more and more inferior.

My mom thinks i'm antisocial. She said if i don't invite friends over soon that she's going to ground me. She never had a problem with me not inviting people over before when we were in the old house. I have to try out again for cheer next week, I'm so scared. Being in cheer this year has been one of the best learning experiences I could ever have asked for. Although things have been rough, we've gone through 3 coaches, one of which who was shot, a school district who doesn't care about us, a girl who just found out that she has a blood clot in her brain and can't cheerlead anymore let alone do anything, and we still managed to go to nationals. If that doesn't teach you perservance I don't know what does. After going through all the tears, the screaming, the fights, enduring it all and not making it onto varsity again, that would crush me like none other. For once in my life I felt like I accomplished something this year, I managed to be the only girl on the squad to never get into one fight with anyone else, be torn between 3 different friends who were mad at eachother. I've learned so much, about being a good friend, never quitting or giving up when we knew that we were a helpless case. 
We got a new coach who actually knows what she's doing. The school board finally let us get a coach who wasn't a teacher at tucson high already. For awhile we were all ready to just give up because the school told us that we could only still have a team if they found a teacher here who would be our coach, now how many teachers do you know who would just come out of the woodwork and say "yeah I'm an english teacher but I also know about cheerleading." not many! We've already had two coaches who had no background experience whatsoever and we were on the verge of giving up because we knew that we would have to continue to be doing everything ourselves, which was fine some of the time except when some girls didn't want other girls to be superior over them and name themselves the leaders. Thats what started all the drama. And we managed to get our bid to nationals all by ourselves when we had to make up a new routine at 9 o'clock t night before competition because two girls were uneligible. Then wonderful Tanisha came along, our new coach. She knows about cheerleading and is so organized, she saved us, ever since she came along, theres been no more tears, no more fights, and we've improved on everything. After all of this, I'd do it again in a heartbeat. The only thing that could work against me is my age, they might say (well she has time) and put me on JV again.    I would be so upset if that happened, because I know that I have improved so much, and never have I once dropped a girl, never have I once started drama, I got hit in the mouth, my mouth was full of blood and I said "lets do it again". I've bonded with everyone intensly and I was the most unhappy person when I was on JV, they were horrible people, treated me and a few other girls like (excuse me but) like shit. I understand that with all that has happened with disciplinary problems why they want to do try outs again but I think we've gone through enough.

I just wrote 10 paragraphs about my philosophies and I was about to update and my computer froze, soon I will update but I can't go through all that again...today. So I'll just say something brief.
I just want to say how thankful I am to have such good friends. 
I also wanted to say thank you to a certain friend for opening mu eyes to different views and such, and you all may not know it but I learn wonderful things, important things from you everyday. I've learned that all the selfishness and shallow ideals are nothing and to find the deeper part of everyone. You know, I hear these girls and they're talking about how they think thats its okay to be with a guy who only likes the for their body, and I TOTALLY disagree, "High School is just for messing around," they say...I just think thats wasting your valuable feelings on someone who's just using you. 
I also have learned to be yourself. Heres a good example: there was this guy that I had a huge crush on for awhile, and as soon as I discovered that I really did like him, I started to find myself agreeing to things that he said, just to agree with them, not because I actually did...and then I stopped liking him because I couldn't stand how he cussed so much. He used very derogatory words and I couldn't stand it. So after that I just stopped caring what he thought, and now he likes me. And I respect myself enough to tell him that his cussing makes me uncomfortable, and now he doesn't curse in front of me, because he respects me and the way I feel. 
The thing is, I was miserable when I was trying to please him all the time. It's not doing anyone good, and I am truely blessed to have friends who mostly have morals like me and how everyday never ceas to amaze me with their brilliance.
Thank you to all of you,
I love you
~Corinne
